Process Engineer

Celanese

- Bishop, TX 78343

Celanese is a Fortune 500 global chemical innovation company that engineers and manufactures chemicals used in products essential to everyday living. Headquartered in Dallas, TX, we employ over 7,700 dedicated people working between 43 facilities across 18 countries. We are committed to employee growth and creating shareholder value to ensure continued opportunities make a difference. Our company focuses on the safety of its employees, provides competitive compensation (including benefits starting day 1), and emphasizes giving back to the community. For more information about Celanese and our products please visit www.celanese.com

Summary: Engineer will be trained on various Celanese engineering practices and best industry practices. They will be involved in process safety, operations and technical design opportunities. Position ensures achievement of 4 core principles when providing process engineering support. The position provides technical expertise and knowledge to the manufacturing process of the unit. Implement new technologies, new processes, and raw materials.

Ensures achievement of 4 core principles when providing process engineering support. Provide technical expertise and knowledge to the manufacturing process of the unit. Implement new technologies, new processes, and raw materials. Drive the safety culture from occupational to process safety. Deliver productivity based on training provided based on technology and engineering. Lead MOCs and heavy involvment during scheduled turnarounds to provide technical support.

Strongly motivated individual who is driven to develop knowledge and skills and produce results. Demonstrate ability to handle multiple priorities. Ability to analyze complex situations and think both strategically and creatively. Ability to work in a team based environment. Strong computer skills. Effective communication skills.

